Reasoning: The paper deals with 3D reconstruction from single view images, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves learning a mapping from 2D images to 3D point cloud embeddings, which could fall under graphics (cs.GR). The use of a probabilistic latent space and diversity loss suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) and/or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) component to the approach. Finally, the problem of 3D reconstruction from a single image could also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO).
